      <section eId="sec_44_6_40">
        <num>44-6-40</num>
        <content>
          <p>An estate may be granted upon either express or implied conditions. The estate shall commence, be enlarged, or be defeated upon the performance or breach of the conditions.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2275; Code 1868, § 2268; Code 1873, § 2294; Code 1882, § 2294; Civil Code 1895, § 3136; Civil Code 1910, § 3716; Code 1933, § 85-901.)</p>
